data.title: Convert Burundian Francs (BIF) and Euros (EUR): Currency Exchange Rate Conversion Calculator
data.meta_description: Calculator to convert money in Burundian Franc (BIF) to and from Euro (EUR) using up to date exchange rates.
data.text:
This Burundian Franc and Euro convertor is up to date with exchange rates from August 18, 2024.

Enter the amount to be converted in the box to the left of Burundian Franc. Use "Swap currencies" to make Euro the default currency. Click on Euros or Burundian Francs to convert between that currency and all other currencies.

The Burundian Franc is the currency in Burundi (BI, BDI). The Euro is the currency in Andorra (AD, AND), Austria (AT, AUT), Belgium (BE, BEL), Estonia (EE, EST), Europe (EU, the European Union), Finland (FI, FIN), France (FR, FRA), Germany (DE, DEU), Greece (GR, GRC), Ireland (IE, IRL), Italy (IT, ITA), Luxembourg (LU, LUX), Latvia (LV, LVA), Monaco (MC, MCO), Malta (MT, MLT), Netherlands (NL, NLD), Portugal (PT, PRT), San Marino (SM, SMR), Slovenia (SI, SVN), Slovakia (Slovak Republic, SK, SVK), Spain (ES, ESP), Vatican City (Holy See, VA, VAT), French Guiana (GF, GUF), Guadeloupe (GP, GLP), Martinique (MQ, MTQ), and Reunion (RE, REU). The symbol for BIF can be written FBu. The symbol for EUR can be written â‚¬. The Burundian Franc is divided into 100 centimes. The Euro is divided into 100 cents. The exchange rate for the Burundian Franc was last updated on June 5, 2023 from MSN. The exchange rate for the Euro was last updated on August 18, 2024 from The International Monetary Fund. The BIF conversion factor has 5 significant digits. The EUR conversion factor has 6 significant digits.
